WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.060 --> 00:00:04.140
In this tutorial I'll show you how to

00:00:01.979 --> 00:00:05.940
make any property react to audio in

00:00:04.140 --> 00:00:07.560
After Effects so let's get to it here

00:00:05.940 --> 00:00:09.300
you can see I have a composition with

00:00:07.560 --> 00:00:11.460
some music on a timeline once you add

00:00:09.300 --> 00:00:13.139
your music or any audio layer right

00:00:11.460 --> 00:00:15.599
click on it going to keyframe assistant

00:00:13.139 --> 00:00:17.220
convert audio to keyframes that will

00:00:15.599 --> 00:00:19.380
create a new layer called audio

00:00:17.220 --> 00:00:21.960
amplitude so let's expand its properties

00:00:19.380 --> 00:00:24.000
go into effects here you'll find left

00:00:21.960 --> 00:00:25.740
right and both channels you could select

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:27.480
left and right channels and press delete

00:00:25.740 --> 00:00:29.880
to delete them and leave just the both

00:00:27.480 --> 00:00:31.859
channels if we expand this drop down you

00:00:29.880 --> 00:00:34.260
will see that the slider inside of both

00:00:31.859 --> 00:00:36.480
channels has keyframes with different

00:00:34.260 --> 00:00:38.700
values and we can use this set of the

00:00:36.480 --> 00:00:40.920
keyframes to make any property react to

00:00:38.700 --> 00:00:43.079
the audio now let me bring the logo to

00:00:40.920 --> 00:00:44.879
the timeline then press s on the

00:00:43.079 --> 00:00:46.079
keyboard to bring its scale now I'm

00:00:44.879 --> 00:00:47.760
going to hold the ALT key on the

00:00:46.079 --> 00:00:50.219
keyboard and left click on the stopwatch

00:00:47.760 --> 00:00:53.039
for the scale that will enable us to

00:00:50.219 --> 00:00:56.399
add Expressions here so we want to find

00:00:53.039 --> 00:00:58.440
the spiral pick whip click and drag it on top

00:00:56.399 --> 00:01:00.000
of the slider then release it and that

00:00:58.440 --> 00:01:02.640
will fill up the code for us if you

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:05.159
click away you will see that the logo

00:01:02.640 --> 00:01:07.140
will be reacting to the audio but you'll

00:01:05.159 --> 00:01:09.180
notice that the logo has shrunk to

00:01:07.140 --> 00:01:11.580
this tiny size that is because the

00:01:09.180 --> 00:01:14.159
default scale of 100% is no longer being

00:01:11.580 --> 00:01:16.439
accounted for and it is solely driven by

00:01:14.159 --> 00:01:18.720
this expression so we can add that scale

00:01:16.439 --> 00:01:21.360
into this expression so let's click here

00:01:18.720 --> 00:01:24.180
go into the end of the expression type

00:01:21.360 --> 00:01:26.759
+[100,100]

00:01:24.180 --> 00:01:28.259
+[100,100] click away and

00:01:26.759 --> 00:01:30.119
you'll see the logo is back to its

00:01:28.259 --> 00:01:32.460
original size and the reaction of the

00:01:30.119 --> 00:01:34.439
audio is added on top of it and this

00:01:32.460 --> 00:01:36.420
approach is required for settings that

00:01:34.439 --> 00:01:39.180
have multiple properties in this case

00:01:36.420 --> 00:01:41.100
scale has X and Y scale and for the

00:01:39.180 --> 00:01:43.439
settings that have one single

00:01:41.100 --> 00:01:45.900
property it is a lot easier so let me

00:01:43.439 --> 00:01:48.720
remove this expression and open effects

00:01:45.900 --> 00:01:51.180
and preset search for transform and add it

00:01:48.720 --> 00:01:53.520
to the logo layer and in the effect

00:01:51.180 --> 00:01:56.100
controls you'll find scale but this one

00:01:53.520 --> 00:01:58.020
has one single property scale so I'm

00:01:56.100 --> 00:02:00.360
going to hold the alt left click on the

00:01:58.020 --> 00:02:01.799
stopwatch for scale and then before I

00:02:00.360 --> 00:02:04.920
drag the pick whip I'm going to type

00:02:01.799 --> 00:02:07.380
value+ and then I'm going to drag

00:02:04.920 --> 00:02:09.959
this pick whip to the slider again here

00:02:07.380 --> 00:02:12.120
let go and that fills up the code so if

00:02:09.959 --> 00:02:14.640
we click away you will see that the logo

00:02:12.120 --> 00:02:17.400
is reacting in the same way and

00:02:14.640 --> 00:02:20.280
it has stayed the same in terms of scale

00:02:17.400 --> 00:02:22.500
since we added the value+ and this

00:02:20.280 --> 00:02:25.080
value stands for any value that you set

00:02:22.500 --> 00:02:27.420
in the scale at any given moment and the

00:02:25.080 --> 00:02:28.260
reaction of the audio is being added on

00:02:27.420 --> 00:02:30.420
top

00:02:28.260 --> 00:02:32.700
and I'll see if you wanted to increase

00:02:30.420 --> 00:02:37.379
or decrease the extent of the reaction

00:02:32.700 --> 00:02:40.500
you could add say times two or divide by

00:02:37.379 --> 00:02:42.780
2 at the end of the expression or like

00:02:40.500 --> 00:02:45.120
any other value then click away and

00:02:42.780 --> 00:02:47.220
that would increase the reaction

00:02:45.120 --> 00:02:49.620
say times two that would make it like

00:02:47.220 --> 00:02:52.860
times two pretty much or you can put any

00:02:49.620 --> 00:02:55.260
value here to exaggerate the effect if

00:02:52.860 --> 00:02:57.060
you want to so 4 will be too much and

00:02:55.260 --> 00:02:59.040
also one important thing I would

00:02:57.060 --> 00:03:01.319
like to cover here is creating a

00:02:59.040 --> 00:03:03.840
specific reaction threshold and we can

00:03:01.319 --> 00:03:06.480
do that in the slider itself so let's

00:03:03.840 --> 00:03:08.940
hold the alt and click on the slider

00:03:06.480 --> 00:03:12.900
stopwatch and then here we're going to

00:03:08.940 --> 00:03:15.780
type linear(value,)

00:03:12.900 --> 00:03:17.819
now let's open the graph editor right

00:03:15.780 --> 00:03:19.620
click and make sure the edit value graph

00:03:17.819 --> 00:03:21.300
is selected so we can see the values of

00:03:19.620 --> 00:03:23.400
the keyframes and here you will see

00:03:21.300 --> 00:03:25.560
these keyframes with all the different

00:03:23.400 --> 00:03:27.780
values and you will need to identify the

00:03:25.560 --> 00:03:29.940
lower end of the threshold so let's come

00:03:27.780 --> 00:03:31.860
here and and look at these values and

00:03:29.940 --> 00:03:34.019
these are like six point something five

00:03:31.860 --> 00:03:36.659
point something so let's go ahead and

00:03:34.019 --> 00:03:40.500
select seven to be a low threshold so

00:03:36.659 --> 00:03:43.140
type in after a comma type seven and add

00:03:40.500 --> 00:03:45.720
another comma and now we need to find

00:03:43.140 --> 00:03:48.080
the high end of the threshold so here

00:03:45.720 --> 00:03:51.060
this is 20 24

00:03:48.080 --> 00:03:53.819
23 so you could choose any value pretty

00:03:51.060 --> 00:03:57.360
much and let me just choose 20 so type

00:03:53.819 --> 00:04:00.120
20 comma and I will need to give these

00:03:57.360 --> 00:04:02.819
values a meaning so as our low

00:04:00.120 --> 00:04:04.980
threshold we've chosen seven so what

00:04:02.819 --> 00:04:07.319
we're trying to do here is anything that

00:04:04.980 --> 00:04:09.540
is 7 or less in these values will be

00:04:07.319 --> 00:04:13.439
considered as 0 and we'll get no

00:04:09.540 --> 00:04:17.639
reaction at all and so let's do zero so

00:04:13.439 --> 00:04:20.400
it is zero then comma and 20 is the high

00:04:17.639 --> 00:04:22.919
end of the threshold so if we add 20

00:04:20.400 --> 00:04:25.259
here and then click away well let's

00:04:22.919 --> 00:04:28.860
bring back the slider so what this means

00:04:25.259 --> 00:04:31.259
is 20 at this point is the maximum the

00:04:28.860 --> 00:04:34.320
reaction would go so even at points

00:04:31.259 --> 00:04:36.600
where the value is 24 or 23 it would

00:04:34.320 --> 00:04:39.960
still be considered a 20 and will not go

00:04:36.600 --> 00:04:42.180
higher than 20. and now if we preview or

00:04:39.960 --> 00:04:43.979
like go to the point like the there are

00:04:42.180 --> 00:04:46.560
keyframes here so if we come here you

00:04:43.979 --> 00:04:48.180
can see logo is not reacting and even at

00:04:46.560 --> 00:04:50.040
this point if we bring the time

00:04:48.180 --> 00:04:53.040
indicator here you can see the logo is

00:04:50.040 --> 00:04:55.620
not reacting and only when it enters the

00:04:53.040 --> 00:04:57.660
threshold that we've set you can see

00:04:55.620 --> 00:05:00.840
we're getting the reaction so if we come

00:04:57.660 --> 00:05:03.360
to this point where the value is 20 you

00:05:00.840 --> 00:05:05.520
can see the logo is like big now if we

00:05:03.360 --> 00:05:07.979
go to the point where it says 24 you'll

00:05:05.520 --> 00:05:10.740
see the logo or the value of the slider

00:05:07.979 --> 00:05:13.259
is still set to 20 and no matter like

00:05:10.740 --> 00:05:15.660
where you go past the 20 it will still

00:05:13.259 --> 00:05:17.340
be considered a 20. and at this point I

00:05:15.660 --> 00:05:19.680
think I've covered every important

00:05:17.340 --> 00:05:21.360
aspect of the properties reacting to

00:05:19.680 --> 00:05:22.919
audio in After Effects I hope you

00:05:21.360 --> 00:05:24.660
learned something new and enjoyed this

00:05:22.919 --> 00:05:27.860
tutorial thank you guys for watching and

00:05:24.660 --> 00:05:27.860
I'll see the next one peace out

